name: "Tentacle Cluster", 12x18" Archival Print
description:
"Tentacle Cluster" is part of a series of cluster-like drawings. This one includes two of my favorite things, cephalopods and booze. This print comes ready to pop into your favorite 12x18" store-bought frame.

About Printing
Unless otherwise specified, these images are printed using a Canon Pro9000 Wide Format Photographic Inkjet Printer on Epson Ultra-Premium Presentation Matte Paper. Often referred to as "Giclée", these premium prints are "open-editions" and shipped signed by the artist.

About Shipping
Prints are shipped rolled in a tube. I ship at a flat-rate of $5. via USPS Priority Mail (for US Domestic orders) + Delivery Confirmation unless requested otherwise. Please note that all international orders are shipped USPS First Class International at a flat rate of $10 unless specifically arranged otherwise. Please allow 1 to 2 weeks for delivery although I'll try my best to get your orders out to you as soon as possible.

name: King of Kings, 11.7x16.5" Archival Print
description:
When I was a kid, sometimes I'd sneak into my grandparents' room and snoop around. Their house was full of unusual antiques, figurines, books, and other treasures. On one of my explorations I found a pack of nudie cards in my grandpa's dresser. Years later I told my mother about finding the pack of cards and it turns out that she used to sneak in there and look at them too. Now I own Grandpa's "Good Luck" card set and it always reminds me of home.
